cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with hand pose estimation from RGB images using depth information. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as hand pose estimation is an important task in robotics for human-robot interaction. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the paper proposes a method that uses privileged learning to improve the performance of pose estimation from RGB images. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is likely as the paper proposes a method that uses both external large-scale depth image datasets and paired depth and RGB images as privileged information at training time to improve the performance of pose estimation from RGB images. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper deals with hand pose estimation from RGB images, which is a common task in multimedia applications such as virtual reality and gaming.
